2. Are “Layers of Reality” Arbitrary?

Your alphabet analogy is interesting.

The alphabet is an arbitrary ordering of symbols, but it’s still useful because it organizes information consistently.

The layers we talked about are somewhat similar.

They’re not necessarily fundamental “levels of reality,” but they’re levels where different kinds of rules dominate.

For example:

Layer	Dominant rules
physics	physical laws
biology	evolution
societies	institutions
culture	meaning systems

Each layer emerges from the one below but has its own patterns.

Scientists call this emergence.

⸻

Why We Use Layers

Layers help manage complexity.

A biologist doesn’t need to simulate every atom to study ecosystems.

Similarly:
	•	historians study societies
	•	economists study markets
	•	physicists study particles

All of those perspectives are valid.

The layers aren’t fake—they’re useful lenses.

⸻

The Important Insight

Reality probably doesn’t come with pre-labeled layers.

Instead, humans discover stable patterns and build conceptual layers around them.

So the layers are partly:

features of reality
+
tools for understanding


